==English==

===Phrase===
#The sentence previously passed on those guilty of [[high treason]].

====Usage Note====
Strictly, the phrase should be drawn hanged and quartered, as part of the sentence was that the guilty party should be [[draw]]n (''dethratur'') to the place of execution on a [[hurdle]] or behind a horse's tail. Later the guilty party was disembowled (''devalatur'') before being beheaded and quartered (''decapitur et decolletur''); hence the second use of the word draw.

According to official records on 19th October 1685, John Fernley, William Ring and Henry Cornish, were given the following sentence.
:"You must, every one of you, be had back to the place from whence you came, and from there, you must be drawn to the place of execution, and there you must severally be hanged by the necks everyone of you till you are almost dead; and then you must be cut down, your entrails must be taken out and burnt before your faces, your several heads to be cut off and your bodies divided into four parts, and these to be disposed at the pleasure of of the King and the Lord have mercy on your souls."

